ias","date":"April 6, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn Ziyad reported: Wahb ibn Munabbih, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cWhoever places his lusts beneath his feet, Satan will flee from his shadow. Whoever overcomes his whims by his forbearance, that one is among the victorious scholars.\u201d Source: H\u0323ilyat al-Awliya\u0304\u2019 4\/60 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0632\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u062f\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34603,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/11\/30\/ibn-masud-fear-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":38103,"position":1},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Taqwa: Sinful to show anger when told to fear Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 30, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Zayd ibn Wahb reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cIt is enough sin for a man to get angry when he is told to fear Allah.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r 8588 Grade: Rijal al-Sahih (narrators are reliable) according to Al-Haythami \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0632\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0628\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25140,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadi